#: ../../H/hosed.rst:5
msgid "hosed"
msgstr "hosed"

#: ../../H/hosed.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../H/hosed.rst:9
msgid ""
"Same as :ref:`down`\\. Used primarily by Unix hackers. Humorous: also "
"implies a condition thought to be relatively easy to reverse. Probably "
"derived from the Canadian slang ‘hoser’ popularized by the Bob and Doug "
"Mackenzie skits on SCTV, but this usage predated SCTV by years in hackerdom "
"(it was certainly already live at CMU in the 1970s). See :ref:`hose`\\. It "
"is also widely used of people in the mainstream sense of ‘in an extremely "
"unfortunate situation’."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`down`\\ "
"と同じ。主にUnixハッカーによって使われる。滑稽:また、元に戻すのが比較的容易だと考えられる状態も含意する。おそらくSCTVのBob and Doug"
" "
"Mackenzieのコントで広まったカナダのスラング‘hoser’に由来するが、この用法はハッカーダムではSCTVより何年も前から使われていた(CMUでは1970年代には確かにすでに生きていた)。\\"
" :ref:`hose`\\ を参照。また主流の意味での‘極めて不運な状況にある’人々についても広く使われる。"

#: ../../H/hosed.rst:16
msgid ""
"Once upon a time, a Cray that had been experiencing periodic difficulties "
"crashed, and it was announced to have been hosed. It was discovered that the"
" crash was due to the disconnection of some coolant hoses. The problem was "
"corrected, and users were then assured that everything was OK because the "
"system had been rehosed. See also :ref:`dehose`\\."
msgstr ""
"むかしむかし、周期的な問題を経験していたCrayがクラッシュし、hosedされたと発表された。クラッシュは冷却ホースのいくつかが外れたことによるものだと判明した。問題は修正され、その後ユーザーはシステムがrehosedされたのですべてOKだと保証された。\\"
" :ref:`dehose`\\ も参照。"
